Class nsint

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Number
      • com.minenash.nsint
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class nsint
extends java.lang.Number

    NonStandard Integer

    The NonStandard Integer class adds the ability to have integers in other bases.
    Since:
    2016-11-13
    Version:
    1.2.3
    Author:
    Minenash
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString(int displayMethod)
        Returns a string representation of the NonStandard Integer.

        DisplayMethods:
        0 - The number, then the base in subscript. Example: 21001₃
        1 - The number, then the word "base" in small caps, then the base in subscript. Example: 21001ʙᴀsᴇ₃
        2 - The number, then the word "base" in small caps, then the base. Example: 21001ʙᴀsᴇ3
        3 - The number, then the letter 'B', then the base. Example: 21001B3
        4 - The number, then ", base", then the base. Example: 21001, Base 3

        Parameters:
        displayMethod - How the user wants to use it.
        Returns:
        The String representation of the NonStandard Integer.
